<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain's Ruano-Pascual Claims Budapest Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Virginia Ruano-Pascual of Spain
took the Budapest Wonmen's Open on Sunday, beating Italy's Silvia
Farina 6-4, 4-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Ruano-Pascual, the seventh seed, won the first set against the
temperamental and inconsistent Italian.
</P>
<P>
Farina lost her cool several times and made a lot of unforced
errors, but she regained her composure to take the second set.
</P>
<P>
But after losing the first game of the decider when she led
40-0, she went to pieces and Ruano-Pascual had an easy ride to 5-0.
</P>
<P>
Farina staged a belated recovery and saved three match points
as she fought back to 5-3, but had no answer when Ruano-Pascual
took a 40-0 lead in the next game and easily took her first match
point for the title.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
