<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coulthard Takes San Marino Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 26 (xinhua) -- David Coulthard in his McLaren
Sunday won the San Marin Grand Prix and revive his world champion
hopes in Imola, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Leading from start to finish, Coulthard looked to be in trouble
as Michael Schumacher in his Ferrari began to reel him in over the
closing laps.
</P>
<P>
From a 23-second gap between the two rivals, the 27-year-old
Scot saw the German close to within five seconds but even
Schumacher could not grab a dramatic last lap victory.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Eddie Irvine in the second Ferrari held off Jacques
Villeneuve to finish third having raced with a pain-killing
injection after suffering back muscle spasm "after five laps in
the car."
</P>
<P>
Former champion Damon Hill was forced to retire just three laps
from the finish when lying eighth for Jordan while Johnny Herbert
also finished early when his Sauber developed mechanical problems.
</P>
<P>
Coulthard's teammate Mika Hakkinen, leader in this season's
title race, was forced to call it a day on lap 17 with gearbox
trouble. The Finn heads the championship standings with 26 points.
</P>
<P>
Coulthard has moved up into second place with 23 points with
Schumacher third with 20 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
