<HEADLINE> Tanzania Marks 34th Union Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa inspected an honor of guard Sunday at the National
Stadium here in the celebration of the 34 anniversary of the
union of Tanganyika and Zanzibar.
</P>
<P>
The honor of guard was mounted by the Tanzania People's
Defense Forces, the police force, and the Prisons and National
Services between 10 am and 11 am.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa, who is also the Commander-In-Chief of the Tanzanian
Armed Forces did not make any speeches at the function.
</P>
<P>
Attending the ceremony were also Tanzanian Vice-President Omar
Ali Juma, Zanzibar President Salmin Amour, Prime Minister
Frederick Sumaye and foreign envoys.
</P>
<P>
Tanganyika and Zanzibar was united on April 26, 1964, forming
the United Republic of Tanganyika and Zanzibar. The country was
renamed as the United Republic of Tanzania on October 29 in the
same year.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, congratulatory messages have poured
in from state leaders of the United States, Cuba, Portugal,
Brazil, Ethiopia and other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
