<HEADLINE> 17th Hong Kong Film Awards Presented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony for presentation of
the 17th Hong Kong Film Awards was held at the Grand Theater of
Hong Kong Culture Center Sunday night, with Nicetop Independent
Ltd.'s film "Made in Hong Kong" winning the Best Film Award.
</P>
<P>
"Made in Hong Kong", a film concerning some social problems
existing among Hong Kong youngsters, also won Best Director award.
The film was produced by well-known singer-actor Andy Lau and
directed by Fruit Chan.
</P>
<P>
Tony Leung Chiu Wai who stars in "Happy Together" won Best
Actor Award and Maggie Cheung in "The Soong Sisters" was awarded
Best Actress.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Film Awards are organized by the Hong Kong Film
Awards Association. Candidates of this year's 16 awards are
selected from among the films produced in Hong Kong in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The final decisions were made by professional adjudicators
after two rounds of evaluation which lasted for four months.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region was present at the Awarding Ceremony.
</P>
</TEXT>
