<HEADLINE> Collision of 2 Planes Kills 4 in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Two amateur-piloted small planes
collided with each other Sunday in Bretagne in western France,
killing two pilots and two passengers on board, Agence
France-Presse (AFP) quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
Two old "Fouga Magister" planes bumped into each other in the
commune of Saint-Dominique about 30 kilometers north of Rennes,
the regional capital of Bretagne, from where they took off.
</P>
<P>
The two planes were bought by a team of amateur pilots a few
years ago from the French air force, which used them for training
pilots and conducting patrol flights, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
Among the killed was Yves Duval, the head of the amateurs' team
engaged in a training program "Yankee Delta." 
</P>
</TEXT>
