<HEADLINE> French Train Conductors Union Threatens to Disrupt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- An independent trade union of train
conductors of France Sunday threatened to disrupt the
transportation during the 98 France World Cup Football season, if
their demand for pay raise is not met.
</P>
<P>
The union, called FGAAC, disrupted some trains transport lines
in Paris and between Paris and Lyon by staging strike Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The FGAAC said that the state railway company SNCF should raise
their salaries by from 500 to 1,500 francs (83 to 249 U.S.
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
