<DOCNO> XIE19980427.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-26 17:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran, Syria Call for Israeli Withdrawal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 26 (Xinhua) -- In a joint communique issued here
Sunday, Iran and Syria voiced their support for Lebanon in
demanding a speedy and unconditional withdrawal of Israeli troops
from its territory.
</P>
<P>
The communique was released by the Iranian official news
agency at the end of a visit by Syrian First Vice President
Abdul-Halim Khaddam, who arrived here Saturday afternoon to
coordinate with Iranian officials.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, Iran and Syria termed the recent Israeli
offer for conditional withdrawal from south Lebanon as a
conspiracy aimed at diverting world public opinion, stirring up
tension in Lebanon and hurting the destiny of Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet decided on April 1 to accept the United
Nations Resolution 425, saying it would pull out its troops from
south Lebanon after negotiating security arrangement with Beirut.
</P>
<P>
The offer was firmly rejected by Lebanon and Syria.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Syria urged the U.N. Security Council and
U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan to end Israel's occupation of
Muslim and Arab lands, including Jerusalem, in an effort to
establish security and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
They reiterated their "all-out support" for the national and
Islamic resistance against Israeli occupation, terming the
resistance as "legitimate struggle consistent with the
international laws."
</P>
<P>
Expressing concern about the military cooperation between
Turkey and Israel, the two countries said their cooperation could
poise a threat to regional states, especially the neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Expecting Turkey to reconsider its cooperation with Israel, the
two countries urged Ankara to expand cooperation with Muslim
states, especially with its neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, Syria condemned Israel's accusation that
Iran was developing nuclear weapons, saying the Israeli move was
aimed at diverting world public opinion from its own stockpile
of weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Both Iran and Syria, stressing the need for cleansing the
Mideast region from any atomic arms and other weapons of mass
destruction, called on the international community to force Israel
to bring its atomic activities under supervision of the
International Atomic Energy Agency.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of stability and security in the
region, Iran and Syria voiced hope for closer cooperation among
states in the region.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam wound up his visit and return home Sunday afternoon.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
