<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Seizes 2,100 Kilograms of Opium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Iran's anti-drug forces seized
2,100 kilograms of opium from a camel caravan in the northeastern
province of Khorasan, a security commander announced on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian official news agency IRNA, the camel
caravan was stopped by the security forces in Nahbandan, head of
the political-ideological department of Khorasan's provincial
security forces Ismail Baqerpour said.
</P>
<P>
Without giving the specific date of the drug haul,
Baqerpour said that although the smugglers escaped, 20 camels,
several light weapons and some ammunitions were confiscated.
</P>
<P>
According to Iran's anti-drug headquarters, Iran seized 187
tonnes of various narcotics during the past Iranian year (ending
March 20), 83 percent of which were opium, 11 percent
morphine, 5 percent hashish and 1 percent heroin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
