<HEADLINE> China's PLA Chief of General Staff Arrives in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Chief of the General Staff of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) Gen. Fu Quanyou arrived
here Sunday night on a five-day official visit to India aimed at
enhancing mutual contacts and friendship between the two countries
and armed forces.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to India by a chief of the PLA General
Staff and both countries have attached great importance to it.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in India, Gen. Fu Quanyou is expected to call
on Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee, and meet Indian
Defense Minister George Fernandes and chiefs of India's three
armed services to exchange views with them on furthering
interaction and friendship between the two countries and the two
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
With the relations between the two neighboring countries
improved and expanded in recent years, exchange of visits between
the two armed forces has also increased, pushing the two
countries' ties to a new level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
