<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Holds Wedding Ceremony fo;28 Couples </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A grand wedding ceremony
for 128 couples was held Sunday in Addis Ababa, the capital of
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The wedding ceremony was held in accordance with a project
sponsored by different governmental and non-governmental
organizations in the country, including the Ministry of Labour
and Social Affairs, the women's bureau in the prime minister's
office, and Addis Ababa city social affairs office.
</P>
<P>
According to the project's manager Nur Nassir, the project is
organized to encourage minimum expense in wedding ceremonies and
help the newly married to form a family free from debt.
</P>
<P>
Organizations and enterprises in the country have extended
their assistance to the wedding.
</P>
<P>
The organizers said that the 128 couples were selected from
more than 300 applications representing different professions in
governmental and non-governmental organizations and came from
various regions and Addis ababa city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
