<HEADLINE> Greece, Armenia Urged to Cooperate Closely </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos Sunday called on Greece and Armenia to cooperate
closely in the wake of economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an event in Athens marking the 83 anniversary of the
genocide of 1.5 million Armenians on April 24, 1915 by Turkey,
Tsohatzopoulos said that in the wake of economic globalization and
the effort of international organizations to create an environment
of security and peace, Greece and Armenia had the duty to develop
their bilateral ties and cooperate closely, the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
He urged Greek businessmen to increase their investment in
Armenia.
</P>
<P>
As for the relations between the two countries, the minister
said that their relations, which were developing rapidly and of a
defense nature, were not aimed against any third country. 
</P>
