<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti New Tenders Law to Include Military Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 26 (Xinhua) -- A senior Kuwaiti official
said on Sunday that the Kuwaiti cabinet is expected to approve a
tender law in two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of State for Cabinet
Affairs Nasser Abdallah Al-Roudhan said the law will cover all
tenders, including military equipment deals.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, foreign arms suppliers will have the chance to
win deals in Kuwait through open tenders.
</P>
<P>
So far, military purchase from foreign suppliers, mainly the
United States, Britain and France, by Kuwait have not been
conducted through open bids.
</P>
<P>
The draft law has been referred to the ministerial Legal
Committee for modifications, Al-Roudhan said, adding that it will
be submitted to the cabinet for endorsement in a maximum two-week
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
