<HEADLINE> Buyers Surge 51 Percent at Asia's Largest Gift Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Close to 40,000 giftware buyers
-- a new record -- stopped and shopped at Asia's largest gift
fair, the Hong Kong Gifts and Houseware Fair '98, according to the
Hong Kong Trade Development Council (HKTDC) here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The total number of visitors at the fair, organized by the
HKTDC from April 15 to 18, increased by 51 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
Of all visitors, 52 percent were from outside Hong Kong. Buyers
from major gift markets in North America and Europe rose by 45.3
percent and 30.5 percent, respectively, while visitors from Asia
increased by 22.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Visitors from emerging markets in Central and South America,
the Middle East and Africa all reported a growth of higher than 50
percent, indicating growth in the potential of these markets.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the fair organizing committee, Jeffrey Lam, said
though clouded by economic downturn in some Asian countries, the
importance of the event as a business opportunity for the giftware
industry was reaffirmed.
</P>
<P>
"The popularity of the event reinforces Hong Kong's role as an
international sourcing center for all kinds of giftware and
household products," he said. 
</P>
