<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Goes Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index went down by 20.68 points on Monday to close at
1,589.85 against last Friday's close at 1,610.53.
</P>
<P>
A total of 41 million shares were traded on Monday against the
44.8 million shares last Friday.
</P>
<P>
There were 43 gainers and 97 losers while share prices of 53
companies remained unchanged in Monday's trading.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 Index closed lower Monday on low trading volumes
caused by punters holding their positions on the news that
Independent Power Producers (IPP) and the government had not
sorted out their differences.
</P>
<P>
Monday morning saw trading mainly in Pakistan Telecom Company
Ltd. (PTCL) stocks as traders held their positions on IPP scrips
as news reached the bourse that no significant development had
taken place in the talks between IPP and the government over
tariff reduction.
</P>
<P>
The government has threatened to cancel IPP projects if tariff
reductions do not take place.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say Monday's trading was dominated by speculative
activity in PTCL scrips. Brokers predicted that the stock market
may see further declines on Tuesday as the energy sector comes in
for another battering. 
</P>
