killed Sunday night by a group of unidentified assailants in a
border village called Mohra Seiri in Mirpur Division of
Pakistan-held Kashmir area.
</P>
<P>
According to a report Monday by the Associated Press of
Pakistan, the 21 people killed were from two families.
</P>
<P>
The report said some unidentified armed men entered the houses
of the two families in Mohra Seiri village near the line of
control in the Samanni Valley of Bhimber District in Mirpur
Division at around 11:15 p.m. Sunday night and gunned down 21
people including women and children.
</P>
<P>
Several others were injured in the attack and two of them were
in serious condition, the report added.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, which has sent the people in Mirpur
Division to panic, local officials rushed to the spot to assess
the situation.
</P>
<P>
Investigation of the incident is now under way.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
