<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Somali Clan Fighting Goes into 4th Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Fighting around the Southern
port of Kismayu seems to be escalating as the armed clashes enter
the fourth day Monday, spreading to territories controlled by the
faction led by Hussein Mohamed Aidid in Lower Jubba region.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest reports, the Majerten Militiamen led
by the son-in-law of Somalia's late dictator, General Mohamed
Said Hirsi Morgan, have been repulsed back for a few kilometers
for the first time since they launched what is seen as a decisive
campaign in eradicating the Marehan militiamen from the region.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Jilib District, 170 km North of Kismayu, indicate
that Colonel Abdullahi Garamgaram, the operation commander and a
well known military official among General Morgan's militia
leaders has been one of the deceased in Sunday's fighting around
the strategic village of Mugambo, 100 km North of Kismayu.
</P>
<P>
However, reports from Kismayu denied the death of Colonel
Garamgaram and there's no independent confirmation.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Garamgaram who led a strong militia battalion with six
battle wagons has made a considerable advance into the
territories controlled by the Marehan militiamen until Sunday
morning, a report said.
</P>
<P>
In this militia advance by the Majerten, a few militia bases
from Hussein Aidid's faction were also overrun.
</P>
<P>
There are conflicting casualties in the fighting between the
two sides. However, radio VHF reports controlled by the Marehan
sub-clan in the region indicate that six of their militiamen were
killed in the fighting Sunday.
</P>
<P>
They also claimed the killing of nine militiamen from the
other side during the fighting on late Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 people have so far been killed and nearly 70
others were wounded since the fighting has intensified four days
ago.
</P>
<P>
The Majerten militiamen have also captured more than 20
prisoners and the villages of Gobwein, Yontoy and Bulo Gudud all
in Lower Jubba region earlier controlled by Marehan militiamen
and Hussein Aidid's faction.
</P>
<P>
These prisoners include four Habar Gidir militiamen from
Hussein Aidid's militia bases in the region.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the new upsurge of fighting is not yet known,
however, clan political analysts said that General Morgan plans
to capture more territories from Hussein Aidid's side so as to
eliminate the Marehans from the region on the one hand and to
stop the current peace talks in Mogadishu on the other.
</P>
<P>
General Morgan has always opposed to the Cairo peace
declaration and he intends to grab some parts of the rich farming
area in Lower Jubba region.
</P>
<P>
Despite the growing concern over the Kismayu fighting in
Mogadishu, it seems that Hussein Aidid's side will be forced to
get involved.
</P>
<P>
There 's also a peace tentative by the clan elders of Biomal
and Galjel of Hawiye tribe, but it is still too soon to talk
about its affects or success. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
