<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Holds Talks with Kirghiz Counterpart  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- It is a priority item for China
in formulating its foreign policy to develop friendly ties with
its bordering countries, President Jiang Zemin said here today in
talks with President of the Kirghiz Republic Askar Akayevich
Akayev.
</P>
<P>
No matter how the world situation changes, this basic policy
will remain unchanged, said Jiang, adding that developing
Sino-Kirghiz friendly relations and cooperation of mutual benefit
accord with the fundamental interests of the peoples of both
countries, and will promote regional peace, stability and
development.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang, historic documents like the five-nation
agreements on improving trust, disarmament and the Sino-Kirghiz
border, of which he and Akayev were two of the signatories in 1996
and 1997, have enhanced the bilateral relationship of mutual trust
in the field of politics and military affairs to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Akayev told Jiang that the agreements which will be signed
after the present talks will lay a solid foundation for the
friendly relations of cooperation between the two countries in the
coming century.
</P>
<P>
The visiting president said that mutual trust has been
bolstered and the range of cooperation broadened since the two
countries forged diplomatic ties six years ago. He expressed
gratitude to China for its support of the Kirghiz Republic's
reforms.
</P>
<P>
China will, as always, support the Kirghiz Republic in its
efforts to safeguard its independent sovereignty, maintain
domestic stability and revitalize its national economy, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation and gratitude to the Kirghiz
Republic and its people for their consistent and clear support of
China on the issues of Taiwan, Tibet and opposing national
separatism.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980427.0056 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Holds Talks with Kirghiz Counterpart  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Akayev reiterated that the Kirghiz Republic stands wholly on
the side of China on the above-mentioned issues, and firmly
opposes national separatism and religious extremism.
</P>
<P>
The Kirghiz Republic has learned from China's successful
experiences in dealing with the relations between ethnic groups,
he added.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral economic and trade relations, Jiang said that,
along with the globalization of the economy, economic factors have
become more and more important in the relationship between
nations. "Further bolstering economic and trade cooperation is the
common task we are facing," Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation between the two countries in recent years has
demonstrated that there are great advantages and potential for
China and the Kirghiz Republic to develop economic and trade
cooperation, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"Both of us are undertaking economic reforms and accelerating
our opening up to the outside, which provides a good opportunity,"
said Jiang, who added that he hoped that enterpreneurs of both
countries would be more pragmatic and increase mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the volume of trade between China and
the Kirghiz Republic has rose 50 percent, which, the visiting
president said he hoped, would be doubled. He expressed confidence
that China would undoubtedly become the most important trade
partner of the Kirghiz Republic in the coming century.
</P>
<P>
On the situation in Central Asia, Jiang said, "We are happy to
see that the Central Asian nations have been focusing on
maintaining social stability, advancing economic reforms,
strengthening regional cooperation and expanding contacts with
other countries since their independence.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two presidents signed a joint declaration
on further developing and deepening the relations of friendly
cooperation between the two countries. Agreements on economic and
trade cooperation, Chinese loans to the Kirghiz Republic, a
certificate of approval on the Sino-Kirghiz Republic border and an
agreement on extradition were also signed.
</P>
<P>
Before the talks, Jiang hosted a welcome ceremony for Akayev
and his party. The two presidents reviewed a guard of honor of the
three services of the Chinese People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Akayev arrived here Sunday at the invitation of Jiang for a
five-day state visit.  
</P>
