<HEADLINE> IOC Plans to Outlaw Marijuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee (IOC) plans to prohibit the use of marijuana and other
recreational drugs, director-general Francois Carrard said in
Sydney on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Carrard said the IOC board had agreed in principle to ban
"social drugs".
</P>
<P>
"Marijuana will be banned, that's for sure," he said.
</P>
<P>
At this year's Winter Olympics in Japan, Canadian snowboarder
Ross Rebagliati was initially stripped of his gold medal after
testing positive for marijuana but was later reinstated.
</P>
<P>
This prompted the IOC to draft up a clear guideline concerning
the recreational drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
