<HEADLINE> Standoff at Restaurant Ends in Massachusetts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A standoff that began with an
apparent robbery at a McDonald's restaurant in Massachusetts ended
Monday morning when one of the two gunmen were killed and another
fled, the Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
More than a dozen people were freed when special police entered
the restaurant at New Bedford, about 100 kilometers south of
Boston. One of the gunmen was found dead in the back of the
restaurant and the other gunman was being sought. He had fled in
a car with two female hostages.
</P>
<P>
The women, including a McDonald's employee, were left in a New
York City motel room, bound and gagged. They managed to free
themselves and call for help.
</P>
<P>
The standoff started at about 9 p.m. Sunday when police arrived
after a report. As officers tried to talk to the two gunmen, they
shot at them and police fired back.
</P>
<P>
One of the gunman fled in a car with the two women when
customers and police were running out.
</P>
<P>
At midnight, SWAT team members opened a door with a key and
found the gunman was dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
