<HEADLINE> HK-US Post-Handover Economic Cooperation Is Good: Volcker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Paul A. Volcker, chairman of
the United States/Hong Kong Economic Cooperation Committee, said
here on Monday that the economic cooperation between Hong Kong and
the United States remains good after Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Volcker, who is here to attend the 13th Plenary Session of the
HK/US &AMP; US/HK Economic Cooperation Committee, told a press
conference that he saw no differences, despite incidental
frictions in China-U.S. trade, in the basic orientations of
economic cooperation with Hong Kong before and after the handover.
</P>
<P>
He said he was happy that the handover was going smoothly and
he anticipated brighter prospects for Hong Kong-U.S. economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Volcker also said that the financial policy of China marked by
its stable exchange rate seems to be successful and there is
something that may be useful to Asian, particularly Southeast
Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
It seems that China has all kinds of strength in terms of trade
position, attractiveness to international capital and the ability
to export, he said.
</P>
<P>
Volcker was chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal
Reserve System of the United States from 1979 to August 1987.
</P>
</TEXT>
