<HEADLINE> Thorpe Beats Klim in 200 Meter Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Australia's world champion Ian
Thorpe swam the fifth-fastest 200 meter freestyle in history on
Monday, beating world titlist Michael Klim of the distance to
second.
</P>
<P>
Thorpe clocked one minute, 47.24 seconds to break the
Commonwealth and national record set by fellow Australian Duncan
Armstrong in 1988.
</P>
<P>
The time was set at a selection meet in Melbourne for the
Australia's team to compete at the Commonwealth Games in Kuala
Lumpur in September.
</P>
<P>
Klim, who won four gold medals at the world championships
earlier this year, clocked 1:47.77 to finish more than half a
second behind Thorpe. 
</P>
