<HEADLINE> Overseas Listing Rejuvenating Chinese Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- So far, 43 Chinese companies
have been listed on stock exchanges in Hong Kong, the United
States and Singapore, raising more than 10 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"The oversea listing has helped Chinese enterprises to
reconstruct and transform according to the requirements of the
international market," said Liu Hongru, former chairman of China
Securities Regulatory Commission.
</P>
<P>
In his speech delivered on a ceremony marking the publishing of
the book, "Review and Outlook of the Overseas Listing of Chinese
Enterprises," held recently in Shunde City in south China's
Guangdong Province, Liu said the overseas listing has forced the
Chinese state enterprises to stand the test of intense competition
in the world market as well as helping them publicize their fame
and reputation.
</P>
<P>
The overseas listing has also equipped a number of Chinese
managers with sound knowledge of the international market and thus
enable them to lead their enterprises to success, Liu said.
</P>
