<HEADLINE> More People Using Mobile Phones in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- At least 5,000 people have become
users of mobile phone service in Macao after the service price
cuts in March, marking a sharp increase, the Macao Daily News
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The number of users of GSM service of the Macao
Telecommunications Company (CTM) increased about 10 percent from
that two months ago. The number of the old-styled analogue mobile
phone service users showed a first positive growth in two years.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the CTM has about 45,000 GSM service users and
10,000 analogue mobile phone users.
</P>
<P>
The CTM cut the monthly cost of analogue mobile phone service
by about half, and the monthly cost of GSM service between 1.61 to
20 percent in March.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted an executive of the CTM as saying that the
company aims to attract 10,000 to 15,000 new mobile phone users
this year.  
</P>
