<HEADLINE> RTHK Produces Diversified Programs to Introduce 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Radio Television Hong Kong
announced here Monday that it will produce a series of TV programs
and organize a number of activities to promote the first
Legislative Council (LegCo) Elections of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Chu Pui-hing, acting director of broadcasting of the RTHK, told
reporters at a press briefing on Monday that the electoral
programs like "Election Forum", "Constituency Forum Q&AMP;A" and
"Functional Constituency Documentary" are aimed to enhance the
understanding of the citizens about the "98 LegCo Elections",
which is scheduled to be held on May 24, through different
formats.
</P>
<P>
Chu said that these programs aim to enable citizens to gain a
better understanding of the backgrounds of all candidates and
provide opportunities for candidates to express their view on
people's livelihood and politics as well as raising queries to
other competitors.
</P>
<P>
On the Election Day, RTHK will provide a live coverage on the
elections in hopes of encouraging voters to exercise their rights
by casting votes enthusiastically, Chu said.
</P>
<P>
On the day after the elections, RTHK will produce a TV special
to cover the results of the elections, he added.
</P>
<P>
Justice Woo Kwok-hing, chairman of the Electoral Affairs
Commission, and candidates of five geographical constituencies
were present at the press conference.
</P>
<P>
There are 166 candidates to run for the LegCo elections. The
first Legislative Council of the HKSAR will comprise 60 members
with 20 of them to be returned through direct election of
geographical constituencies, 30 of them to be chosen from
functional constituencies and 10 to be elected by an 800-strong
Election Committee. 
</P>
