<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Englishman Kerth Blunt was named
head coach for the Chinese Olympic team, the Chinese Football
Association (CFA) announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The CFA also appointed 39-year-old Colin Toal, also from
England, assisant coach of the team.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Olympic team, which will compete in the qualifying
round for the 2000 Olympic Games, has yet to form in April.
</P>
<P>
China qualified for the Olympic finals only once, when it
grabbed a berth at the Seoul Olympic Games in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Blunt, 59, is a top technical official at the English Football
Association National School and has also guided England's under-16
team.
</P>
<P>
The two coaches, expected to arrive in China in May, will be on
a one-year contract. 
