<HEADLINE> CICC Chairman Outlines Success in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Xiaochuan, chairman of
Board of Directors of the China International Capital Corporation
Limited (CICC), the first joint-venture investment banking firm in
China, said here Monday that the CICC has achieved an outstanding
success in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference at the end of a Board of
Directors session held here on Monday, Zhou said the success has
built up the foundation for CICC as an international standard
investment bank in China.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, CICC led or participated in 24 closed transactions,
which included equity financing, merger and acquisition advisory
projects, and debt financing, said Zhou, who is also governor of
China Construction Bank.
</P>
<P>
Important transactions led by CICC in 1997 included the
successful dual-listing of China Telecom (Hong Kong) on the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong and the New York Stock Exchange which raised
4.22 billion U.S. dollars, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
Established on November 8, 1995, the Beijing-based CICC is a
joint-venture between the China Construction Bank and the Morgan
Stanley Dean Witter &AMP; Co., and other Chinese and overseas
partners.
</P>
<P>
"CICC achieved second place in the bookrunner rankings for
equity-related deals in the non-Japan Asia-Pacific region as
measured by International Financing Review for 1997," Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
CICC has established itself as an important participant of
Chinese Government Bond (CGB) markets, he added.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, CICC established its Hong Kong subsidiary to offer
investment banking, sales and trading and research services to
clients, Zhou said, adding that CICC-HK is currently seeking the
approval of its application for the SEHK membership.
</P>
<P>
CICC's total consolidated firm revenue was approximately 50
million U.S. dollars and total pretax earnings in 1997 stand at 30
million U.S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
Currently CICC's Investment Banking Department is broadly
involved in business sectors such as telecom, power, oil and gas,
chemical, transportation, infrastructure and financial
institutions and is working on some major and important projects,
Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
CICC's Direct Investment Department is able to undertake
capital investment or large-scale equity investments with or
without CICC's shareholders, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Sales and Trading Department has successfully procured
seats with Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges and is actively
engaged in CGB proprietary and agency businesses.
</P>
<P>
At the same press conference, John Mack, president of Morgan
Stanley Dean Witter and Co., said: "We are extremely pleased by
the success of this joint venture, which has made great strides
since it was founded three years ago."
</P>
<P>
"We are proud to be able to play a role in the development of
China's capital markets and the restructuring of the Chinese
economy through our involvement in CICC, and look forward to
working with our partners as CICC continues to build on its
success," Mack said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
