<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets up Export-oriented Vegetable Production Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale, export-oriented
enterprise in the suburbs of Shanghai, which is engaged in
producing and selling vegetables in Southeast Asia and western
European nations, has gained a good harvest.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise, involving an investment of 9.8 million
U.S. dollars, was jointly set up by the United States, Australia
and Shanghai, and equipped with modern installations imported from
Israel and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the joint venture is projected to cultivate
1,600 hectares of vegetable-growing areas and produce 15,000 tons
of high-grade vegetables annually. And the output value is
estimated at 700 million yuan and profit at 100-to-150 million
yuan each year.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the first phase of the project, the
venture has put up a 5,000-sq-m hothouse for nursing young
vegetable plants and a 2.2-ha processing center.
</P>
<P>
As forecast, the venture is expected to generate 200 million
yuan in output value this year. And it should reach the designed
production capacity and become a comprehensive company involving
the fields of nursing young plants, processing and exporting
vegetables in the next three-to-five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
