<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Collective Exploitation of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi Monday called upon the Caspian Sea littoral states to
cooperate for proper exploitation of resources in the Caspian Sea.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session of the sixth seminar on Central
Asia and the Caucasus, Kharrazi said the proper exploitation of
the sea's resources requires a legal framework as well as
consultation and trust among the littoral states.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister stressed Iran opposes unilateral use and
exploitation of the sea's resources, warning any such action would
violate the rights of other littoral states.
</P>
<P>
The Caspian Sea was reported to have proven reserves of 16
billion barrels of crude oil and 8.3 billion cubic meters of
natural gas.
</P>
<P>
So far, the five littoral countries, namely Iran, Turkmenistan,
Kazakhstan, Russia and Azerbaijan, have not reached any agreement
on how to exploit the natural resources and to protect the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said at the semimar that Tehran was ready to cooperate
with other Caspian Sea littoral states in construction of
refineries, terminals and laying oil and gas pipelines to develop
the sea.
</P>
<P>
Experts and researchers from 19 countries including Britain,
China, France, Italy, Russia, the U.S., Pakistan and republics of
the Central Asia and the Caucasus attended the two-day
seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
