<DOCNO> XIE19980427.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SIMEX Plans to Expand Equity Index Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore International
Monetary Exchange (SIMEX) announced here on Monday that it will
start trading a Singapore stock index contract in August this
year, and will list equity index contracts related to the stock
markets in Malaysia and Thailand from November 1998.
</P>
<P>
In addition, SIMEX said that futures contracts relating to
other Asian stock markets are being studied and will be added
subsequently.
</P>
<P>
The decision to list a Singapore stock index contract and
expand the range of regional products on SIMEX is in line with the
recent recommendations of the Sub-Committee on Finance and Banking
of the Committee on Singapore's Competitiveness, which comprises
representatives from the financial industry, it said.
</P>
<P>
Victor Liew, Chairman of SIMEX, said, "the listing of a
Singapore stock index contract and other contracts relating to the
stock markets in the region will help strengthen SIMEX's position
as a leading center for trading Asian equity index products."
</P>
<P>
The globalization of the capital markets in Asia has increased
demand for effective risk management instruments among global
traders and investors. The provision of risk management
instruments such as the planned equity index futures contracts
will help develop greater breadth and resilience in regional
capital markets, he said.
</P>
<P>
"By providing hedging opportunities, they can also increase
global investment interest in the underlying stock markets," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore stock index futures contract to be launched in
August will be based on the MSCI (Morgan Stanley Capital
International) Singapore Free Index, which is compiled by MSCI.
</P>
<P>
The MSCI Singapore Free Index is a market
capitalization-weighted index of 37 stocks, which covers 55
percent of the total market capitalization of the Stock Exchange
of Singapore (SES), the SIMEX said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Index has 96 percent correlation with the SES
All-Singapore Index compiled by the SES, and is widely used by
many international investors as a performance benchmark for their
investment portfolio in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The SIMEX also said that the SIMEX MSCI Singapore Index
contract will be traded via the SIMEX Automated Trading System
(ATS), developed and maintained by the SES.
</P>
<P>
"This will facilitate the participation of the stock broking
community in Singapore which is used to electronic trading," Liew
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
