<HEADLINE> Iranian FM: Practical Measures Needed to Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi said here Monday that practical measures are needed to
improve the relations between Iran and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Answering questions at a press conference, Kharrazi denied the
report that the issue of Tehran-Cairo ties was discussed during
the recent visit by Syrian First Vice President Abdul-Halim
Khaddam.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the visit, Khaddam only conveyed Egypt's
interest in improving relations with Iran, but the talks between
Syrian and Iranian officials did not go on details about Iran's
ties with Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam arrived here on Saturday for a two-day visit to
coordinate stances with Iranian officials on the recent Israeli
proposal on conditional withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Both Iran and Syria rejected the Israeli plan and reiterated
their support for Lebanon who has called for a speedy and
unconditional withdrawal of the Israeli forces.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister termed Egypt as a "country with
rich culture," saying that Iran believes the cooperation between
Tehran and Cairo would have positive impacts on the regional
developments since Iran and Egypt are two important countries in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Both Tehran and Cairo have expressed their readiness to
improve their bilateral ties, particularly after the election of
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami, who favors friendly relations
among regional countries
</P>
<P>
However, no specific steps have been taken to realize the
resumption of ties between the two countries, which severed their
diplomatic relations in 1979 after Egypt signed the David Camp
peace accord with Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
