<HEADLINE> Beida Plays A Unique Role In Modern China's History (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Numerous new thoughts -- including democracy, science, equality
between men and women, and marriage freedom -- were also first
spread from Beijing University, the professor said.
</P>
<P>
According to Ren Yanshen, Party Secretary of Beijing
University, Beida was China's first state comprehensive
university. Its foundation was regarded as the start of China's
modern higher education.
</P>
<P>
Since the introduction of reform and opening-up drive, China
has attached great importance to science and technology. Late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping once said that science and technology
are the primary productive forces and, in a recent speech, Chinese
premier Zhu Rongji said that "revitalizing the nation through
science and technology" should be regarded as a basic state policy.
</P>
<P>
"This is another reason to highlight Beida's centennial," Ren
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the past 100 years the university has been
one of China's key educational and scientific research centers,
and the centenary celebration is an important event not only for
Beijing University but also for the entire scientific and
educational communities in China.
</P>
<P>
Ren said the university will carry out its fine tradition of
patriotism, democracy and science in the next century, and speed
up its reform and development to build a vigorous and high-level
university.  
