amir to Iran last December to attend the eighth summit of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference, Kuwaiti ambassador in
Tehran Abdullah Abdulaziz Al-Duwaikh was quoted as saying Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral relations between Kuwait and Iran have been on good
terms. In May 1997, Kuwait and Iran signed a bilateral memorandum
of understanding on all aspects of economic and trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Iran have also been striving to increase their
trade exchanges. Latest statistics show that the trade exchanges
between Iran and Kuwait stood at nearly 100 million U.S. dollars
in 1997. 
