<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Adopts Work Plan for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A meeting attended by the
chairman and vice-chairmen of the National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee here today passed an outline of the committee's
work in 1998, the first year of its term in office.
</P>
<P>
According to the outline, the NPC Standing Committee will step
up legislation, improve supervision, cement ties with NPC deputies
and local people's congresses, and expand contacts with foreign
parliamentary bodies.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Standing Committee will increase the work of
the special committees under the NPC, better publicize the
people's congress system and raise people's awareness of the law.
</P>
<P>
The outline also stated that the Standing Committee would hold
high the Deng Xiaoping Theory, stick to the basic lines of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and conscientiously exercise the
power endowed by the Constitution to safeguard the country's
reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
The meeting approved a plan on the deliberation of draft laws
by NPC Standing Committee members this year. In addition, a report
was presented at the meeting on China's economic situation in the
first quarter of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
