<HEADLINE> FW de Klerk, Pik Botha to Marry Their New Loves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Former South African
President F.W. de Klerk and former foreign minister Pik Botha,
will remarry with new women, the Star daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
De Klerk, 62, announced last week his intention to marry his
Greek love, Elita Georgiadis, saying, "I have already instructed
my attorney to proceed with a divorce action. Mrs. Georgiadis is
likewise busy with a divorce action and we plan to marry each
other when that has been finalized."
</P>
<P>
De Klerk has ruled out any possibly of making up with his
estranged wife of 39 years. Georgiadis was reportedly to leave
her husband Tony, to whom she had been married for 27 years.
</P>
<P>
De Klerk's wife Marike, 60, had made no comment when told of
her husband's statement Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Botha was due to marry a long-time professional friend, South
African Broadcasting Corporation executive producer Ina Jourbet,
on his 66th birthday Monday.
</P>
<P>
The marriage was planned for later, but the couple decided to
bring it forward since Botha is due any day to undergo an
operation for prostate cancer, according to sources closed to
Botha.
</P>
<P>
Botha's first wife, Helena, died two years ago. 
</P>
