<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Beverage Industry Growing Fast (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coconut Palm has developed 51 high-grade products, including 21
items which have won both international and national gold
prizes. The company's natural coconut juice, mango juice and
mineral water have been designated for use at state banquets. The
company has hosted visits by more than 70 ambassadors to China and
over a dozen foreign chiefs of state.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute Coconut Palm's success mainly to the fact
that the "naturalness" of its products caters to worldwide return
to nature trend for beverages.
</P>
<P>
The company's natural coconut juice contains 17 kinds of amino
acids conducive to health, according to the Ministry of
Health. "Coconut juice is nutritious and coconut fat is beneficial
for the treatment of viruses and cancer," according to Dr. Mary
Enig, a well-known U.S. nutritionist.
</P>
<P>
The group's specialists conducted 383 in-depth experiments
before finally developing the company's coconut juice freshness
preservation technique which the Chinese Association for Science
and Technology cites as unique in the world. The technique is
currently registered in China's inland and Hong Kong, the
Philippines, Britain and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The company, the first domestic beverage producer to export
both products and equipment, currently exports the equipment of
its automatic processing lines.
</P>
<P>
China's immature national beverage industry has witnessed rapid
development, but nonetheless will require consistent efforts for
future progress, according to the Board Chairman Wang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
