<HEADLINE> 19 Killed by Mud Slides in Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Mudslides killed 19 people,
injured another 16 and left over 400 homeless in Tajikistan, the
Interfax news agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian news agency in a dispatch from Dushanbe, capital of
Tajikistan, said that the Navde village in Garms district has
been destroyed completely.
</P>
<P>
Another village near Nurek has been evacuated by the
Emergencies Committee and local authorities, Tajik Deputy Prime
Minister Ismat Eshmirzoyev was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Eshmirzoyev said that Tajikistan has not experienced a natural
disaster of such scale for 30 years.
</P>
<P>
The disaster occurred because of a torrential rain and
hailstorm last Sunday which has destroyed or damaged half of all
gardens and vineyards.
</P>
<P>
Mudslides destroyed hundreds of hectares of cotton fields, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains are estimated to continue till the end of May.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik government has decided to call for international aid
to fight the disaster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
