<DOCNO> XIE19980427.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beihai Air Quality Leads China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A recent report by the China
Environment Monitoring Station shows that Beihai, located in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, led the list of 30
Chinese cities in terms of air quality.
</P>
<P>
Beihai and Zhuhai in Guangdong Province and Xiamen in Fujian
Province led the list respective air pollution indices of 31, 37
and 40, the reports says.
</P>
<P>
Beihai is one of 46 cities listed by the central government
for regular air pollution monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The city's air quality has consistently rated good or excellent
in line with the national standards, with TSP representing the
main pollutant.
</P>
<P>
Local tourism officials hope the report will serve to attract
more tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
