<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Collective Sector Expands Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Collective enterprises, a major
part of the public owned economic sector in Tianjin, have grown at
an average annual rate of 30 percent over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Collective industrial and commercial firms in north China's
largest port city recorded a 1997 output value of 29 billion yuan,
up 32 percent on the previous year, with profits rising by 19
percent to 1.46 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By now, some 1,820 collective enterprises have introduced modern
enterprise system which has been implemented in conjunction with
re-organization, transformations and ownership transfer.
</P>
<P>
A number of profitable enterprises have expanded by acquiring
small-sized state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the Tianma Group purchased a small state-owned
enterprise and invested five million yuan in developing new
products and exploring new markets. Eight other groups have
followed Tianma's suit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
