<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Host Sixth Asian Folk Arts Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Asian Folk Arts
Festival will be held in Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province, on
Oct. 12-21.
</P>
<P>
The festival will coincide with the 29th annual meeting of the
International Council of the Organization of Folk Festivals
(ICOFF), an international non-governmental group designed to
magnify its member nations' traditional cultures and increase
protection of each nation's traditional folk arts.
</P>
<P>
The festival will feature performances of folk art troupes from
16 member countries in the Asian-Pacific region. Stage
performances, a street parade, exhibitions of traditional crafts
and a lamp show will also add special flavor.
</P>
<P>
Both events will be sponsored by the Chinese Mass Culture Study
Society and the government of Kunming, a city renowned for its
historic sites and picturesque scenes.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1970, the ICOFF now has 74 member countries
worldwide. It holds an annual meeting in one of its member
nations on a regular basis, and hosts World Folk Arts Festival
every four years and an Asian Folk Arts Festival every two years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Mass Culture Study Society joined the ICOFF in 1993
on behalf of China, and has since dispatched 10 folk arts troupes
to perform in similar festivals worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
