<HEADLINE> Blood Shortage in UK Could Force Operations to Be Canceled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Blood supplies in Britain are
running dangerously low as hospitals set about cutting waiting
list, the National Blood Authority (NBA) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Operations are to be canceled as the nation's blood supplies
reach crisis levels. A nationwide campaign, including emergency
radio appeals, has been launched with a call for more donors.
</P>
<P>
Stocks have fallen in a week from 16,000 to 14,000 units, only
1,000 above the level at which non-urgent operations would have to
be canceled, according to a spokesman from the NBA.
</P>
<P>
Hospitals are trying to reduce their waiting lists as they have
money available to carry out operations in the new financial year,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
However, the NBA admits that owing to the blood shortage, it
has canceled and reduced blood supplies to some hospitals, mainly
in the Midland, the south and the west of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
