<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plummet In Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices tumbled in Tokyo
Monday on arbitrage-linked selling while buyers retreated to the
sidelines.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the
First Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange plunged 361.29 points,
or 2.26 percent from last Friday's close to 15,649.95 points.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, lost 25.13 points, or 2.03 percent to
1,213.82.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section decreased to an estimated 320
million shares from Friday's 370 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Traders said selling pressure brought down stock prices in a
thin market.
</P>
<P>
A brisk advance in the U.S. dollar against the yen in the
currency market also dampened investor sentiment, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, losers far
outnumbered gainers 984 to 196, with 93 remaining unchanged.
</P>
