foreign exchange bureaus shall daily announce their rates of
exchange to the public, the latest issue of English weekly
Eritrea Profile reported.
</P>
<P>
Tekie Beyene, Governor of the Bank of Eritrea, said effective
May 1, 1998 all government and private institutions and
individuals shall obtain foreign currency from banks and foreign
exchange bureaus only.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of Nakfa has been 7.2 against the U.S.
Dollar since it was issued in November 1997. 
