the issue of IRA prisoners. This issue would be discussed also
with all the other political parties involved.
</P>
<P>
"We will also be visiting the political prisoners in their
cells, implementing the peace agreement and advancing the call
for the cease-fire," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kgalema Motlanthe, ANC Secretary-General, said the South
African government had also been asked by the Democratic Republic
of Congo to explain to the developed countries the difficulties
the D.R. Congo's government was facing in trying to reconstruct a
country ravaged by 32 years of dictatorship and civil war.
</P>
<P>
"They (Laurent Kabila's government) want us to convey the
message to the outside world that it is not easy to hold
elections under such condition," Motlanthe said. 
