<HEADLINE> India's Woolen Exports Increase in 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- India's exports of wool and
woolens increased from the target of 18290 million rupees to
19482.9 million rupees (about 500 million U.S. dollars) in the
financial year 1997-98, the Financial Express reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, the 20 percent growth came mainly due to the rupee
depreciation and it recorded only 13 percent increase in terms of
dollar value.
</P>
<P>
Over a third of India's wool and woolen exports comes from
woolen ready-made garments which grew by 29 percent in the
just-ended financial year (from April 1, 1997 to March 31, 1998).
</P>
<P>
Woolen yarn exports grew at 15 percent last year but fallen
short of its target, according to the financial daily. 
</P>
