<HEADLINE> High-Tech Joint Venture Insured Against Property Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The three largest Chinese
insurance companies have jointly written a property insurance
policy for the country's largest electronics high-tech company
under construction, the Shanghai Huahong-NEC Electronics Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The company, which involves one billion U.S. dollars in
investment, was jointly funded by the Shanghai Huahong
Micro-Electronics Co. Ltd. and Japan-based NEC. It will go into
trial operation in February of 1999 with a monthly capacity of
20,000 pieces of 0.35 to 0.5 micron silicon chips a month.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese insurers -- PICC Property, China Pacific Insurance
Company and China Ping An Insurance Company -- promised to
compensate any property losses of the project that might occur
during its construction period due to natural disasters, incidents
and third-party liabilities.
</P>
<P>
The total premium the project is valued at more than 700
million U.S. dollars, against risks in construction and
transportation.  
</P>
