<HEADLINE> Hebei Benefits from Technology Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four new and high
technology import items enabled north China's Hebei Province to
achieve a total added output value of 200 million US dollars and
1.4 billion yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province invited over 1,600 experts to work in the fields
of culture, education, technology and management during the year,
up 12 percent on the 1996.
</P>
<P>
Hebei sent over 2,000 people abroad for advanced studies or
joint research with their counterparts in a number of countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
The Local agricultural department imported 2,000 types of
cereal crops and invited 50 foreign experts to provide instruction
related to the hybridization of vegetable and control over insect
infestations and plant diseases.
</P>
<P>
The over 60 types of agricultural technology items introduced
to solve 82 key problems and develop 51 new agricultural products
earned 250 million yuan in increased production.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 researchers were to sent the United States to study
virus-free technology. They have since returned and have
successfully developed detoxified strawberry seedlings which have
been introduced to 80 percent of Hebei's strawberry fields. 
