<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai University Bans Alcohol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Institute of
Physical Education will prohibit on-campus sales and consumption
of wine, beer and spirits effective May 1.
</P>
<P>
Today's Wenhui Daily reported that the institute will become
the first institution of higher education in Shanghai to ban
alcoholic drinks.
</P>
<P>
Three students died from alcohol-related incidents in recent
years, and over 90 percent of students welcome the ban.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation will prohibit all campus restaurants, dinning
rooms and stores from selling alcohol.
</P>
<P>
Students will be prohibited from consuming alcohol during their
four years of study, with the ban equally applicable to sports
training and sports events.
</P>
<P>
Even teachers and staffers will be prohibited from consuming
alcohol during office hours and lunch periods.
</P>
<P>
Students found in violation of the ban three times will be
forced to leave the institute.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai institute is one of the country's few universities
or colleges to ban alcohol. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
