<HEADLINE> 4 Israeli Soldiers Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Four Israeli soldiers were
wounded Monday morning in a roadside bomb blast by Lebanese
guerrillas in south Lebanon, Lebanese Voice of the People radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at the Shahein Valley in the western
sector of the Israeli occupied south Lebanon when an armored
Israeli patrol was passing by, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Guerrilla sources claimed the responsibility for the bomb attack
at 3:05 a.m. (0005 GMT), saying it killed and wounded several
Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
They said some of its fighters also attacked Israeli posts at
the hilltop of Radar and Burat inside the so-called Israeli
security zone.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security sources in the country's southern coastal
city of Tyre, near the occupied zone, confirmed that after the
bomb explosion, fierce clashes between guerrillas and Israeli
occupying forces broke out in the area.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying an artillery bombardment, Israeli warplanes
swooped down upon the suspected guerrilla bases on the mountainous
areas between the village of Majda Zoun and Yaetir, just north of
the occupied zone, in retaliation for the guerrillas' attack, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the 1,200-square-kilometer self-styled security
zone in south Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting
its northern areas from Lebanese guerrilla cross-border attack.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanese resistance movement spearheaded by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has been engaged in a
guerrillas war trying to dislodge some 2,000 Israeli occupying
forces from the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
