<HEADLINE> Heron Flock to Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- A flock of 10,000 heron roosting
in the downtown section of Tianjin have enriched the tint of
spring in the major north China port city.
</P>
<P>
Trees located in a wooded area near a local hotel are filled
with nests, with female heron brooding and males engaged in
leisurely flight
</P>
<P>
Local biologists say that heron normally live in central and
southwest China, and noted the rarity of thousands of herons
gathering in the downtown area of a major metropolis in north
China.
</P>
<P>
The specialists attribute the phenomenon to Tianjin's improving
ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
Local forestry departments are engaged in an active effort to
protect the birds. 
</P>
