<HEADLINE> China To Build High-Speed Beijing-Shanghai Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a high-speed
railway linking Beijing and Shanghai will begin in 2000.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Shanghai Railway Administration Bureau noted
the high-speed railway will be part of the country's efforts to
build an efficient railway network in eastern areas.
</P>
<P>
The existing railway network in east China has failed to meet
the growing demand for railway transportation resulting from
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is also preparing to begin construction of a second
railway station.
</P>
<P>
Bureau plans call for the construction of 14 key railway
projects, including a new railway station in Hangzhou, the 270-km
Jinhua-Wenzhou Railway in Zhejiang Province, the Fuzhou-Xiamen
Railway in Fujian, the Nanjing-Xi'an Railway and the
Tongling-Jiujiang Railway.
</P>
<P>
The bureau will invest 2.4 billion yuan in related projects
during 1998. 
</P>
