<HEADLINE> Henan Natural Population Growth Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 natural population
growth rate for Henan, China's most populous province, stood at
7.67 per thousand, some 2.39 per thousand lower than the national
rate.
</P>
<P>
Widespread publicity concerning the family planning policy
enabled Henan to reduce the number of births by 325,000.
</P>
<P>
The province has helped 1.6 million single child families in
rural areas live a better life by granting subsidies and providing
training in agronomy.
</P>
<P>
The average per capita income for related families was 20
percent higher than that for families with more than one child.
</P>
<P>
Henan population stood at 92.43 million by the end of 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
