<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Base for Fluorine Replacement Under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's largest
production base for R-134a, a replacement for fluorine refrigerant,
commenced recently at the Jinghe Industrial Park in Xi'an, capital
of northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The project will be carried out at an estimated cost of 210
million yuan, with first phase scheduled for completion in
December this year. The 200 ton designed annual production
capacity for the first phase will rise to 10,000 tons upon
completion of the second phase project in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The base will end China's total dependence on imported R-134a
and will strike a balance between total supply and demand.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, China committed itself to reducing the production and
consumption of fluorine refrigerant, in a bid to reduce emissions
of fluorine products which contribute to the greenhouse
effect. Efforts have since centered on replacing fluorine
refrigerant with R-134a, a harmless and non-poisonous refrigerant
imported from abroad. The development of China's own R-134a passed
technological assessments in January 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
