<HEADLINE> Lodges to be Set up In Colombo For Domestic Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lanka government planned
to set up a number of lodging houses in Colombo for visitors from
the northern and eastern parts of the country, sources from the
Ministry of Social Services said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will be in charge of the project, said the
sources, adding that there are 5,000 to 7,500 persons who come to
Colombo from the northern and eastern parts of the country each
month for treatment, visiting relatives, foreign travel,
employment and education.
</P>
<P>
No proper accommodation was available to these domestic
arrivals. At present there are some lodges in Colombo and the
suburbs, which do not provide standard facilities to its
customers. The lodge owners do not pay serious attention to
identities of their customers.
</P>
<P>
They were merely interested in profit making. In future these
lodges would have to register with the ministry to ensure that
proper ventilation and basic amenities be available, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
They added the lodges to be set up by the state in the city and
the suburbs will ensure enough space, fresh air, standard toilet
facilities and tight security. 
