<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Tackles Salt Water Intrusion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 27 (Xinhua) -- This coastal city in northeast
China's Liaoning Province is drawing up a plan to solve the
problem of salt water leeching into underground water tables.
</P>
<P>
Resulting from overuse of underground water, ten places,
covering 220 sq km, in the city suffer from salt water
intrusion.
</P>
<P>
In some places wells have had to be closed because of
increasing salinization of underground water.
</P>
<P>
Experts have noted that the density of wells in the city is too
high, at six to seven per sq km.
</P>
<P>
To solve the problem, the local government invested three
billion yuan in pumping water to the city from the Biliu River 150
km away.
</P>
<P>
Completed last year, the project has raised the city's water
supply to 1.2 million tons per day from 1994's 800,000 tons and is
expected to provide enough water for the city in the next century.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the city has adopted a series of water-saving
measures such as limiting the scale of urban construction, and
issuing permits for the use of water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980427.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Avalanche Kills Three Mountaineers in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Three Italian mountaineers were
killed and the other three miraculously survived on Sunday after
the six were hit by an avalanche in climbing peak Corno Grande on
the east of Rome.
</P>
<P>
Local reports said that the six people slipped off the 100
meters-high cliff on the occurance of the snowslide. Three were
killed on site.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the avalanche resulted from an unusual rise
of temperature in the last two days following a heavy snowfall,
which leaves the new snow to break away from the ice mountain.
</P>
</TEXT>
