<HEADLINE> Computer Network Helps Find Jobs In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- People in Shanghai used to go to
job markets to look for work, or place ads in the papers, or knock
on doors, but the new computer network has proven itself to be
more modern and more efficient.
</P>
<P>
The computer network was set up by the Shanghai Municipal Labor
Bureau and 24 job brokers early last year. People who use it and
fail to find a job can simply keep using the net, which is linked
up to more than 200 training schools in the city as well, so that
people can get information about further training.
</P>
<P>
In just a few months, over 10,000 people in 56 different
professions have sent their resumes over the net or registered for
training, and more than 6,000 people have gotten some kind of
training.  
</P>
