<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Traffic Accident in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 26 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people were killed and
30 others wounded when a bus fell down from a seven-meter-high
bridge in the southeast Spanish province of Alicante on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It was learnt here that there were 53 passengers on board the
ill-fated bus. Most of them were old-aged Spanish people living in
Paris.
</P>
<P>
Initial police investigations said the accident was probably
caused by slippery roads after rain.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been rushed to hospitals for treatment.
</P>
</TEXT>
