<HEADLINE> Bailey Beaten in 100 Meters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 26 (Xinhua) -- World record holder
Donovan Bailey of Canada was beaten by Chile's Sebastian Keitel in
the 100 meters race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Keitel, South America's 100-meter record holder, clocked 10.10
seconds to win the title, beating Bailey to the second place with
a time of 10.13, which was way off his world record of 9.86
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Claudinei Quirino da Silva finished third with a time of 10.21.
</P>
<P>
Bailey is expected to run again in the May 3 Gran Prix track
event in Rio de Janeiro. 
</P>
</TEXT>
