<HEADLINE> Courier Wins U.S. Clay Court Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 26 (Xinhua) -- America's Jim Courier beat
top-seeded and defending champion Michael Chang 7-5, 3-6, 7-5 on
Sunday to win the U.S. Men's Clay Court Championships in Orlando.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Courier evened his all-time series record with
Chang to 11-11 and ended tha latter's run of success in recent
matches between the two. Chang had won five of their last six
encounters.
</P>
<P>
Courier won three titles in 1997 and won the Davis Cup three
weeks ago. Sunday's victory added his career titles to 23,
including back-to-back wins in the French Open in 1991-92 and
Australian Open in 1992-93.
</P>
<P>
Chang, with 31 career tournament titles, has been locked in a
medal drought since last July when he took the Legg Mason Classic
in Washington, D.C. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
