<HEADLINE> Xinhua News Agency Purchases Software From CA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS, April 26 (Xinhua) Xinhua News Agency, the leading
news provider in China, has selected Unicenter TNG, a key product
of the Computer Associates International, Inc. (CA) of U.S, to
manage its worldwide news editing systems.
</P>
<P>
A formal agreement was signed today at New Orleans, a southern
port city in the U.S., where CA is holding its annual user
conference. After signing the agreement with Charles B. Wang,
chairman and chief executive officer of CA, Chen Mingxiang, chief
engineer of the Technology Bureau of Xinhua told the reporter that
"We will use the new software to optimize our IT (information
technology) resources to serve our worldwide operations and help
position Xinhua for future growth to become one of the leaders in
the global news market."
</P>
<P>
The software costs Xinhua about 100,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua's IT environment encompasses different platforms and
will include more than 2,000 PCs, and various applications and
databases. Unicenter TNG will protect all of Xinhua's desktop
assets as well as help secure the critical information stored
throughout the enterprise. Through Unicenter TNG's Business
Process Views, Xinhua's systems administrators can monitor and
manage their systems, networks, databases and applications from a
business process.
</P>
<P>
Also signing the purchasing agreements with CA here today
included a number of other companies, such as the Stock Exchange
of Singapore, Hyundai Heavy Industries, a major shipbuilder of the
Republic of Korea, ADI Corporation, Taiwan's major computer
display manufacturer, and Duskin Co., Ltd., Japan's first
franchise chain for janitorial and household dust control
services.
</P>
<P>
Unicenter TNG is a product CA has been pushing hard since its
launching late last year. It has been learned here that CA has
sold its Unicenter TNG to a number of news services in Beijing,
including the China Central Television (CCTV) and the Radio
Beijing International. 
</P>
</TEXT>
