<HEADLINE> Kiriyenko: New Russian Government to be Shaped by </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian new prime minister Sergei
Kiriyenko Sunday promised that a new Russian government is to be
shaped by April 29.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Russian television show Zerkalo the
newly-appointed premier said he will submit proposal on the
Cabinet structure and a number of ministerial appointments to the
President on Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the submission Kiriyenko would exchange views with the
leaders of State Duma factions on the Cabinet selections on
Monday, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, he intends to ask the president for more time
to choose worthy candidates for the new Cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The new premier plans to invite parliament deputies to work for
the government and there will be several candidates to each post.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko predicted that many politicians and economists might
be dissatisfied with government staff selection. But, he said, "I
am ready for that" after announcing government appointments he
might come under "attack" and fall victim to "provocations".
</P>
<P>
He also noted that all power branches can work on the economic
situation in Russia calmly and without emotions, since the
political instability ended.
</P>
<P>
"The main fundamental principle is to learn living within
means. Our spending should correspond to our revenues. We are
working to increase the revenues and make the spending more
efficient," Kiriyenko said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
